Preparations are underway at Toka Primary School in Bloemfontein ahead of the launch of the ANC’s Letsema campaign lead by ANC President Cyril Ramaphosa. Ramaphosa is expected to engage with communities at the school around midday. The Letsema campaign aims to renew the ruling party’s social contract with voters and get party members and volunteers to address challenges in their communities. Ramaphosa will kickstart his visit to the city of roses with a visit to a cleaning campaign followed by an inspection of work is underway to fill up potholes. Ramaphosa’s latest visit to the ailing Mangaung Metro comes two weeks after his Presidential Imbizo. @MYANC President @CyrilRamaphosa will on Saturday, 23 April 2022, launch the #Letsema campaign. President Ramaphosa is expected to use the launch to outline the objectives of the #Letsema Campaign which is about the #renewal of the organization’s social contract with the people. pic.twitter.com/Ix7INeASC7 — African National Congress (@MYANC) April 22, 2022 